Hi Team,
Hope you have been well. We have been working in the background with the local Pakistan IBM team to get you answers for your questions. I understand now that you have met with Adeel recently and the specifics of the scope for Open-CE were discussed.
Since the Open-CE repositories are out of support scope of the Linux Support team, therefore I will go ahead and close out this case by the end of the day.
Thank you in advance for your understanding!
Kind regards,
Mohamed AbouRehab

Hi Team,
Hope you have been well. We have been working in the background with the local Pakistan IBM team to get you answers for your questions. I understand now that you have met with Adeel recently. Please let me know if there are still any further questions that you would like to discuss with the Linux support team regarding this issue and I will be happy to assist. If not, let me know if we can go ahead and close out this case.
Kind regards,
Mohamed AbouRehab

##### Variables ####
export EDITOR=/usr/bin/nvim

#### Terminal ####
eval "$(starship init bash)" # Set up startship prompt
eval "$(fzf --bash)"         # Set up fzf key bindings and fuzzy completion
eval "$(zoxide init bash)"   # Setup zoxide
shopt -s direxpand

#### fzf Colorscheme ####
export FZF_DEFAULT_OPTS=" \
--color=bg+:#363a4f,spinner:#f4dbd6,hl:#ed8796 \
--color=fg:#cad3f5,header:#ed8796,info:#c6a0f6,pointer:#f4dbd6 \
--color=marker:#b7bdf8,fg+:#cad3f5,prompt:#c6a0f6,hl+:#ed8796 \
--color=selected-bg:#494d64 \
--multi"

### System Aliases ####
alias ssh='kitten ssh '
# alias ls='ls -a --color=auto --hyperlink=auto '
alias bat='bat --color=always -pp '
alias cat='bat'
alias fzf='fzf -m --preview="bat --color=always {}" --bind "enter:become(nvim {})"'
alias cd='z '
alias ls="eza "

rga-fzf() {
  rga -Sl $1 | fzf
}
